This paper deals with software testing and defect prediction, which are core topics in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper focuses on identifying methods with low fault risk, which involves analyzing code metrics and applying association rule mining, indicating a possible connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD). The use of machine learning techniques for defect prediction suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
